if you have tor disabled you won't peer with onion addressed peers,
if you have tor enabled you'll peer with onion addressed peers and clearnet peers,
enabling yggdrasil or cjdns or something of the sorts will allow you to peer with others in that same network.

TOR always mode closes your fileserver port and redirects ALL traffic through the tor network, that is, you won't be able to directly peer with clearnet peers but through tor, you won't be able to peer with local peers unless there's a path to local peers through tor (which still sends traffic through internet and cripples what speedup you could get from LAN access) and you won't either be able to peer with yggdrasil or cjdns nodes unless somehow tor network knows how to route to them. For the latter, I don't know if it requires your tor exit node to be yggdrassil/cjdns capable or if that's more of a limitation of the network as of now. It may be achievable though I'm not aware of how.

